  • public class TranscannoExporterTest
extends org.corpus_tools.pepper.testFramework.PepperExporterTest
    This is a dummy implementation of a JUnit test for testing the TranscannoExporter class. Feel free to adapt and enhance this test class for real tests to check the work of your importer. If you are not confirm with JUnit, please have a look at http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/JUnit/article.html.
    Please note, that the test class is derived from PepperExporterTest. The usage of this class should simplfy your work and allows you to test only your single importer in the Pepper environment.

    • Method Detail

      • setUp

        public void setUp()
        This method is called by the JUnit environment each time before a test case starts. So each time a method annotated with @Test is called. This enables, that each method could run in its own environment being not influenced by before or after running test cases.

      • test_DummyImplementation

        public void test_DummyImplementation()
        This is a test to check the correct work of our dummy implementation. This test is supposed to show the usage of JUnit and to give some impressions how to check simple things of the created salt model.
        You can create as many test cases as you like, just create further methods having the annotation "@Test". Note that it is very helpful, to give them self explaining names and a short JavaDoc explaining their purpose. This could help very much, when searching for bugs or extending the tests.
        In our case, we just test, if correct number of corpora and documents was created, if all corpora have got a meta-annotation and if each document-structure contains the right number of nodes and relations.
